name: Phil Donahue
summary: Phil Donahue, the trailblazing television talk show host, passed away at the age of 88. Donahue's influential program, "The Phil Donahue Show," ran from 1970 to 1996, and became known for its candid discussions on controversial topics and its impact on daytime television. Often referred to as the "King of Daytime Talk," Donahue's show tackled issues ranging from social justice to politics, breaking barriers in television journalism and captivating audiences with its open and thought-provoking format. Donahue's legacy as a pioneer in talk show hosting has cemented his place in television history.

name: 49ers
summary: The San Francisco 49ers secured a 16-10 victory over the New Orleans Saints in their second preseason game. Notably, starting quarterback Trey Lance and head coach Kyle Shanahan were absent due to injuries. Backup quarterback Brock Purdy and assistant coach Anthony Lynn led the 49ers to victory. Tight end Jake Tonges had a strong performance, catching three passes for 41 yards and a touchdown. The 49ers are now preparing for their third preseason game against the Steelers, amidst contract talks with receiver Brandon Aiyuk. Meanwhile, the Steelers have reportedly acquired Aiyuk in a trade deal, pending Aiyuk's decision on a long-term contract offer from the 49ers.

name: Monkeypox outbreak
summary: The World Health Organization (WHO) has declared the ongoing global outbreak of mpox, formerly known as monkeypox, a public health emergency of international concern. This signifies a heightened level of global alert due to the rapid spread of the virus. While the outbreak initially emerged in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC), it has since spread to other African countries and beyond. The declaration by the WHO aims to coordinate global efforts to contain the virus's transmission and mitigate its health impacts, particularly in light of the emergence of a new variant. The outbreak has prompted the Africa CDC to declare mpox a public health emergency of continental security, highlighting the need for coordinated efforts across the African continent. As the virus continues to spread worldwide, health agencies underscore the importance of preventive measures and collaboration to effectively curb its transmission.

name: Trayon White
summary: D.C. Councilmember Trayon White has been arrested by the FBI on a federal bribery charge. The Department of Justice alleges that White accepted $156,000 in bribes in exchange for influencing legislation. White, a Ward 8 Democrat, has been a member of the Council since 2017. He is the second D.C. Councilmember to be arrested on corruption charges in recent years. In 2010, Harry Thomas Jr. was convicted of bribery and sentenced to three years in prison.

name: Stephon Gilmore
summary: Stephon Gilmore, a five-time Pro Bowl cornerback who played for the Dallas Cowboys last season, has agreed to a one-year contract worth up to $10 million with the Minnesota Vikings. After initially visiting the Vikings but leaving without a deal, Gilmore has now finalized the agreement. The Vikings have been seeking to strengthen their cornerback position and Gilmore's addition will provide them with a veteran presence and leadership.

name: Michigan International Speedway
summary: Due to inclement weather, the NASCAR Cup Series race at Michigan International Speedway (MIS) was postponed on Saturday. The race, originally scheduled to start at 3:00 PM ET, was delayed several times before being officially called off at 8:22 PM ET. This marks the second consecutive year that the race at MIS has been postponed due to weather. Tyler Reddick of Richard Childress Racing won the rain-shortened ARCA Menards Series Henry Ford Health 200 at MIS on Saturday evening.

name: Steelers
summary: In the second preseason game of the NFL, the Buffalo Bills defeated the Pittsburgh Steelers with a score of 9 to 3. The Steelers' offense struggled under quarterbacks Mitchell Trubisky and Kenny Pickett, while the Bills' defense had a strong performance. Steelers running back Jaylen Warren is expected to miss multiple weeks due to a hamstring injury, and his status for the first week of the regular season is uncertain. Meanwhile, Steelers wide receiver Anthony Miller was released by the team. The game was available to watch through various livestream options.

name: Full moon
summary: This August, stargazers will witness a celestial spectacle as we experience not one but four consecutive supermoons. The first of these, known as the Blue Moon, will illuminate the night sky on Monday, followed by three additional supermoons in the coming months. This rare event, where multiple supermoons occur in a row, is a result of the Moon's orbit and its alignment with the Earth and Sun. Supermoons appear larger and brighter than typical full moons, casting an ethereal glow across the night. Don't miss this opportunity to marvel at the beauty of the celestial sphere as we witness a series of supermoons that will culminate in August's Blue Supermoon, also known as the Sturgeon Moon.
